Class ViewersTraceabilityQueries

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.viatra.query.runtime.api.impl.BaseQueryGroup
      • org.eclipse.viatra.query.runtime.api.impl.BaseGeneratedPatternGroup
        • org.eclipse.viatra.addon.viewers.runtime.model.patterns.ViewersTraceabilityQueries
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IQueryGroup

    public final class ViewersTraceabilityQueries
extends BaseGeneratedPatternGroup
    A pattern group formed of all public patterns defined in ViewersTraceabilityQueries.vql.

    Use the static instance as any org.eclipse.viatra.query.runtime.api.IPatternGroup, to conveniently prepare a VIATRA Query engine for matching all patterns originally defined in file ViewersTraceabilityQueries.vql, in order to achieve better performance than one-by-one on-demand matcher initialization.

    From package org.eclipse.viatra.addon.viewers.runtime.model.patterns, the group contains the definition of the following patterns:

    • param2item
    • param2edge
    • param2containment
    • children
    See Also:
